Mexico Stocks: Grupo Elektra, Soriana, Wal-Mart de Mexico Drop

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-08-25T20:20:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/mexico-stocks-grupo-elektra-soriana-wal-mart-de-mexico-drop.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 2.1 percent to 33,904.38.  Mexican retailers followed global stocks lower amid concern
regulators in  Germany  may impose more restrictions on short
selling.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA* MM), the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , tumbled 7.6
percent to 1,087.87 pesos.  Organizacion Soriana SAB (SORIANAB MM), Mexico’s second-
largest grocery store chain, fell 0.9 percent to 29.94 pesos.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB (WALMEXV MM),  Latin America ’s
largest retailer, slipped 1.4 percent to 32.42 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  